The Sin of profane Swearing, I wonder, what ſhadow of Good, any man can think to get by it. In every other Sin, a man aims at Pleaſure, or 

                     •
                  rofit, or Honour; but the Swearer, as the Chriſtian Poet Sings;




Lets his Soul run for nought, as little fearing;

Were I an Epicure, I could hate Swearing.
